The paper deals with traffic forecasting using deep learning and graph analysis techniques. The use of deep learning and graph analysis techniques suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with behavior prediction, which suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of trajectory prediction in the context of urban traffic scenarios suggests that the paper could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of spectral clustering suggests that the paper could belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
